00:15:24,507 --> 00:15:26,426
{\an8}SHIBAURA INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY

295
00:15:26,509 --> 00:15:32,515
{\an8}TOKYO STUDENTS
GRADUATION DESIGN CONTEST 2016

296
00:15:48,030 --> 00:15:49,449
There he is!

297
00:15:49,532 --> 00:15:51,493
-Hey.
-Where? Oh, Hansan!

298
00:15:52,994 --> 00:15:57,665
Thanks you guys for coming.
This is it right here.

299
00:15:57,749 --> 00:15:59,166
What is it exactly?

300
00:15:59,250 --> 00:16:02,795
My design is for building facilities
for physically disabled people.

301
00:16:03,505 --> 00:16:05,172
You see this model right here?

302
00:16:05,256 --> 00:16:08,635
It's Harajuku at 1/500 scale.

303
00:16:08,718 --> 00:16:10,720
It's at the end of Cat Street.

304
00:16:10,803 --> 00:16:15,391
There actually are facilities
for physically disabled people there.

305
00:16:15,475 --> 00:16:17,059
My design is a reconstructive idea.

306
00:16:17,143 --> 00:16:19,479
I'm suggesting to open these up
to the public.

307
00:16:19,562 --> 00:16:21,814
-You don't usually visit them, right?
-No.

308
00:16:21,898 --> 00:16:26,068
I've proposed an idea to open these up.

309
00:16:26,152 --> 00:16:30,364
There are going to be
nice fashion stores in these spaces.

310
00:16:30,447 --> 00:16:32,408
-Oh, that's cool.
-You see?

311
00:16:32,492 --> 00:16:36,412
Because these facilities will allow people
from the inside and outside to mingle.

312
00:16:36,496 --> 00:16:39,123
When you think about creating
a new Harajuku,

313
00:16:39,206 --> 00:16:41,543
I think facilities like this one
are necessary.

314
00:16:41,626 --> 00:16:43,878
That's my idea.

315
00:16:43,961 --> 00:16:45,630
-You came up with this?
-I did.

316
00:16:45,713 --> 00:16:49,258
-I didn't end up winning, unfortunately.
-Oh, no!

317
00:16:49,341 --> 00:16:53,930
Anyways, everything I've done as a student
has culminated in today.

318
00:16:54,013 --> 00:16:55,181
I see.

319
00:16:55,264 --> 00:16:57,474
-Good job!
-Good job!

320
00:16:57,559 --> 00:16:58,976
Really good job.

321
00:16:59,686 --> 00:17:02,229
It'd be awesome if they build
something like this in Harajuku.

322
00:17:03,480 --> 00:17:06,233
I'd brag about you.

323
00:17:06,317 --> 00:17:09,821
Just you wait.
Someday my designs will be out there.

324
00:17:13,950 --> 00:17:18,329
{\an8}What do I do if I screw this up?
I've never made it before.

325
00:17:18,412 --> 00:17:21,290
-I'm sure Hansan will laugh it off.
-True.

326
00:17:27,880 --> 00:17:30,550
-Wow, awesome!
-Does this look right?

327
00:17:30,633 --> 00:17:33,219
-Paella is supposed to be dry, right?
-Yeah.

328
00:17:38,975 --> 00:17:40,476
-I'm home.
-Welcome home!

329
00:17:40,560 --> 00:17:41,561
What's this?

330
00:17:43,563 --> 00:17:46,273
It's for you.

331
00:17:46,357 --> 00:17:50,361
Hayato made these, didn't he?
Right?

332
00:17:50,987 --> 00:17:53,239
-Wow! Really?
-We did.

333
00:17:54,198 --> 00:17:55,783
That's amazing.

334
00:17:55,867 --> 00:17:57,952
-Want a beer?
-Yeah.

335
00:17:58,995 --> 00:18:00,204
Wow, thanks!

336
00:18:00,287 --> 00:18:02,498
"Good job, Hansan."

337
00:18:03,833 --> 00:18:06,502
{\an8}Misaki did all that.

338
00:18:06,586 --> 00:18:07,629
{\an8}Thank you.

339
00:18:07,712 --> 00:18:10,422
I can't guarantee that it tastes good.

340
00:18:11,507 --> 00:18:14,510
This is great.
It smells so good.

341
00:18:19,265 --> 00:18:20,307
Delicious.

342
00:18:20,975 --> 00:18:22,351
-Really?
-Yay, Riko!

343
00:18:22,434 --> 00:18:25,312
-Thanks! Have as much as you like.
-What is it?

344
00:18:25,396 --> 00:18:27,523
Takikomi rice?

345
00:18:28,565 --> 00:18:30,526
Wait, what's it supposed to be?
It's delicious.

346
00:18:30,610 --> 00:18:33,362
-Well...
-This is actually paella.

347
00:18:33,445 --> 00:18:35,322
Oh, seriously?

348
00:18:38,159 --> 00:18:39,911
Sorry, I didn't mean to offend you.

349
00:18:39,994 --> 00:18:42,914
No worries.
From now on, this is takikomi rice.

350
00:18:44,165 --> 00:18:46,167
Have you cleared everything up
at the contest?

351
00:18:46,250 --> 00:18:48,419
Yup. I wasn't able to wow them though.

352
00:18:48,502 --> 00:18:50,171
-What?
-The judges.

353
00:18:50,254 --> 00:18:51,380
Right.

354
00:18:52,173 --> 00:18:54,508
But to us, you're number one.

355
00:18:54,591 --> 00:18:55,760
Yup.

356
00:18:56,678 --> 00:18:58,262
Thanks, guys.

357
00:18:59,346 --> 00:19:02,516
Sometimes doing my best is not enough.

358
00:19:02,599 --> 00:19:05,269
I have to get credited somehow.

359
00:19:07,021 --> 00:19:09,273
That's the only way in architecture.

360
00:19:09,356 --> 00:19:12,526
You won't get paid
unless you're number one.

361
00:19:13,695 --> 00:19:15,321
Because there's only going to be
one building.

362
00:19:15,404 --> 00:19:17,323
So I've got to be number one.

363
00:19:17,406 --> 00:19:20,534
Someday... I will be.

364
00:19:20,617 --> 00:19:22,036
You will be.

365
00:19:23,037 --> 00:19:25,915
What's next for you?

366
00:19:25,998 --> 00:19:29,585
Well, I should put everything together
into a portfolio...

367
00:19:30,712 --> 00:19:32,672
-and prepare to study abroad.
-Okay.

368
00:19:32,755 --> 00:19:35,299
Will you be going to university abroad?

369
00:19:35,382 --> 00:19:36,801
-Grad school.
-Right.

370
00:19:38,552 --> 00:19:42,181
Well, I'm glad we were able to do this
for you tonight.

371
00:19:42,264 --> 00:19:43,599
Yeah, I really appreciate it.

372
00:19:43,683 --> 00:19:46,268
-You always work so hard.
-Exactly.

373
00:19:46,352 --> 00:19:47,937
Thank you.

