00:25:38,995 --> 00:25:41,498
at my presentation?

486
00:25:42,833 --> 00:25:46,170
It really felt like it was
the end of a chapter,

487
00:25:46,253 --> 00:25:48,214
and that a new chapter's beginning.

488
00:25:50,006 --> 00:25:54,720
So from now on,
I'm my own person.

489
00:25:54,803 --> 00:26:00,016
Both for my career and other challenges,
like studying abroad.

490
00:26:00,101 --> 00:26:03,812
I want to thank you both for everything.

491
00:26:03,895 --> 00:26:08,775
I thought about letting you know sooner...

492
00:26:08,859 --> 00:26:11,653
but I didn't want things to be depressing.

493
00:26:14,115 --> 00:26:15,907
I don't like this.

494
00:26:22,206 --> 00:26:24,291
-Don't cry.
-Please don't go.

495
00:26:26,585 --> 00:26:29,421
-I'll come visit Hawaii with Hikaru.
-You should.

496
00:26:29,505 --> 00:26:31,257
-I will.
-Me too.

497
00:26:31,340 --> 00:26:32,883
You should.

498
00:26:32,966 --> 00:26:35,386
I'm sure you already know this, Arman.

499
00:26:35,469 --> 00:26:38,805
I'm sure I don't have to say this.

500
00:26:39,848 --> 00:26:42,851
Stay the way you are.

501
00:26:43,727 --> 00:26:44,770
Thanks.

502
00:26:44,853 --> 00:26:48,607
I think your true calling
isn't to become a firefighter.

503
00:26:48,690 --> 00:26:52,778
I think it's to stay happy,
just as you are now.

504
00:26:52,861 --> 00:26:55,113
Stay that way.

505
00:26:55,197 --> 00:26:58,116
Live life as the happy man that you are.

506
00:26:58,200 --> 00:27:00,118
I think that would be awesome.

507
00:27:00,202 --> 00:27:02,371
-It's not a title you're after.
-I guess.

508
00:27:03,789 --> 00:27:05,457
Change of plans.

509
00:27:08,377 --> 00:27:10,504
My dream job: Happy.

510
00:27:10,587 --> 00:27:13,215
I think that's cool. Really.

511
00:27:15,008 --> 00:27:18,094
I've learned a lot during my time here.

512
00:27:20,013 --> 00:27:21,223
All right then.

513
00:27:22,224 --> 00:27:23,850
I'm gonna do it.

514
00:27:23,934 --> 00:27:25,394
Do it.

515
00:27:25,477 --> 00:27:26,895
Yeah, do it.

516
00:27:31,775 --> 00:27:33,569
Why is everyone so quiet?

517
00:27:34,820 --> 00:27:36,238
So he's leaving.

518
00:27:37,198 --> 00:27:40,576
Give it a second.
The women are all too shocked to comment.

519
00:27:42,786 --> 00:27:44,162
Are you okay?

520
00:27:46,498 --> 00:27:49,918
What's the matter with everyone?
Seriously!

521
00:27:50,001 --> 00:27:51,753
That's not good.

522
00:27:51,837 --> 00:27:53,964
Why?

523
00:27:54,047 --> 00:27:57,133
This isn't the first time
someone's leaving.

524
00:27:57,218 --> 00:27:58,802
It's called Han Loss.

525
00:27:58,885 --> 00:28:00,762
What's Han Loss?

526
00:28:00,846 --> 00:28:04,266
Did you see Tamosan
genuinely not wanting him to go?

527
00:28:04,350 --> 00:28:08,186
A single tear ran down her cheek
as she said "Please don't go."

528
00:28:08,270 --> 00:28:10,522
He's a legend!

529
00:28:11,398 --> 00:28:12,733
That was intense.

530
00:28:12,816 --> 00:28:15,569
I've never seen anything like that
in real life.

531
00:28:15,652 --> 00:28:17,279
Seriously!

532
00:28:17,363 --> 00:28:20,198
I can't believe
there's actually a man like him.

533
00:28:20,282 --> 00:28:23,494
I seriously don't want him to go.

534
00:28:23,577 --> 00:28:25,871
Oh, right. I should just go with him.

535
00:28:25,954 --> 00:28:27,248
Come again?

536
00:28:30,376 --> 00:28:32,043
That was close, Tokui.

537
00:28:32,127 --> 00:28:34,255
Yeah, she had a deranged
look on her face.

538
00:28:36,382 --> 00:28:42,554
-Remember that bit about Arman's dreams?
-Yeah.

539
00:28:42,638 --> 00:28:44,931
-I thought someone wrote a script.
-Seriously.

540
00:28:45,015 --> 00:28:47,268
He said some really good stuff there.

541
00:28:47,351 --> 00:28:50,103
"You're happy, not a firefighter."

542
00:28:50,186 --> 00:28:52,231
-Yeah, but...
-I wanna say something like that.

543
00:28:52,314 --> 00:28:53,857
What is it?

544
00:28:53,940 --> 00:28:55,609
I'm talking here!

545
00:28:57,444 --> 00:28:58,654
I'm sorry.

546
00:28:59,821 --> 00:29:00,864
You're scaring me.

547
00:29:00,947 --> 00:29:03,074
-Yu isn't usually like that.
-I know, right?

548
00:29:03,158 --> 00:29:04,868
I've never said anything like that before.

549
00:29:04,951 --> 00:29:07,954
-He was perfect from beginning to end.
-He was amazing.

550
00:29:08,038 --> 00:29:11,625
-He hasn't made one mistake.
-Not one! That's perfection, right there.

551
00:29:11,708 --> 00:29:15,337
So next up must be when he's leaving.
He's leaving!

552
00:29:15,421 --> 00:29:17,673
Oh, no, that's right.

553
00:29:17,756 --> 00:29:19,925
-Our last Han.
-Let's see our last Han.

554
00:29:20,008 --> 00:29:22,428
-Wait a second.
-Let's see how he'll part from everyone.

555
00:29:22,511 --> 00:29:24,054
Let me make one thing clear.

556
00:29:24,137 --> 00:29:25,847
Don't talk.

557
00:29:30,394 --> 00:29:32,688
Wow, that was cool.

558
00:29:33,647 --> 00:29:35,023
{\an8}Before we start eating,

559
00:29:35,106 --> 00:29:38,735
{\an8}I have an announcement to make
to you three.

560
00:29:38,819 --> 00:29:41,071
I'm leaving <i>Terrace House</i> tomorrow.

561
00:29:43,574 --> 00:29:46,452
Seriously? I'm still cooking.

562
00:29:46,535 --> 00:29:48,412
I'm no longer a student.

563
00:29:50,080 --> 00:29:52,958
I have to start working.

564
00:29:53,667 --> 00:29:55,836
-I don't want you to.
-Sorry.

565
00:29:55,919 --> 00:29:57,003
But...

566
00:29:57,087 --> 00:30:00,006
It's okay. I'll leave quietly tomorrow.
Let's eat.

567
00:30:00,090 --> 00:30:01,174
Let's eat!

568
00:30:01,257 --> 00:30:02,884
-Let's try not to be sad and eat.
-Agreed.

569
00:30:02,968 --> 00:30:05,346
-Thanks, guys.
-Let's just eat.

570
00:30:05,429 --> 00:30:08,307
This feels like
a very cheerful goodbye party.

571
00:30:08,390 --> 00:30:09,391
Right?

572
00:30:09,475 --> 00:30:12,686
We decided to send him off happy.

573
00:30:14,521 --> 00:30:16,565
Riko, take those dumplings.

574
00:30:16,648 --> 00:30:17,816
Sure.

575
00:30:19,318 --> 00:30:20,444
Thanks, guys.

576
00:30:21,612 --> 00:30:24,072
-Those look amazing!
-Oh, yeah!

577
00:30:25,657 --> 00:30:28,410
-Hansan balanced this group out.
-I know, right?

578
00:30:28,494 --> 00:30:30,579
You brought this group together.

579
00:30:31,079 --> 00:30:33,790
It's hard to not be sad.

580
00:30:33,874 --> 00:30:37,043
This is the universe telling us
to be stronger.

581
00:30:39,170 --> 00:30:41,297
-We've all been relying on you.
-Yeah.

582
00:30:41,382 --> 00:30:43,091
All of us.

583
00:30:43,174 --> 00:30:46,052
You girls are like sisters to me.

584
00:30:46,136 --> 00:30:47,596
All of you.

585
00:30:48,597 --> 00:30:50,599
Take care of them for me, will you?

586
00:30:50,682 --> 00:30:52,601
Wait a minute.

587
00:30:52,684 --> 00:30:54,561
Well, if you girls ever want to talk...

588
00:30:55,061 --> 00:30:56,813
come to me.

589
00:30:59,483 --> 00:31:01,360
-He's pretty...
-Unreliable?

590
00:31:01,443 --> 00:31:02,611
No, he's pretty good.

591
00:31:03,319 --> 00:31:05,781
Don't underestimate him.

592
00:31:08,742 --> 00:31:10,326
Is there anything you want to do
before you leave?

593
00:31:10,411 --> 00:31:11,870
Do I?

594
00:31:11,953 --> 00:31:13,830
-Let's do something.
-Good idea.

595
00:31:16,375 --> 00:31:18,585
It's so cold. For real.

596
00:31:19,252 --> 00:31:22,130
I didn't think I was going to end up
in this pool again.

597
00:31:22,213 --> 00:31:24,716
So thanks, I guess?

598
00:31:24,800 --> 00:31:26,342
-Oh, yeah?
-Get in there.

599
00:31:36,395 --> 00:31:38,188
-Is it really cold?
-Actually, it's not bad.

600
00:31:38,271 --> 00:31:39,815
-Are you sure?
-I'm coming in!

601
00:31:39,898 --> 00:31:41,149
Ready, set, go!

602
00:31:46,196 --> 00:31:47,781
It's so cold.

603
00:31:49,408 --> 00:31:51,952
-Is it really cold?
-What are you doing over there?

604
00:31:52,035 --> 00:31:53,912
-No, please!
-Come on!

605
00:31:59,793 --> 00:32:01,587
This is scary to watch.

606
00:32:03,505 --> 00:32:05,799
-Goodbye party's over!
-Really?

607
00:32:19,438 --> 00:32:20,897
-Morning.
-Hey, good morning.

608
00:32:20,981 --> 00:32:22,398
Hansan...

609
00:32:23,817 --> 00:32:26,612
-You're cleaning.
-Yeah.

610
00:32:26,695 --> 00:32:28,905
You don't have to!

611
00:32:29,448 --> 00:32:32,033
-I'm sorry we were up late last night.
-No worries at all.

612
00:32:32,117 --> 00:32:35,286
There's a ballet competition this month.

613
00:32:36,287 --> 00:32:37,998
I'm going to get into the top three.

614
00:32:38,081 --> 00:32:41,960
I'll be rooting for you,
Momoka Mitsunaga, 21 years old.

615
00:32:43,378 --> 00:32:46,840
-Okay.
-Stay happy, like Arman.

616
00:32:49,718 --> 00:32:50,969
See you later.

617
00:32:51,803 --> 00:32:53,472
-Okay, I'm gonna go now.
-Okay.

618
00:32:54,848 --> 00:32:57,433
-Thank you.
-Thank you, too.

619
00:32:57,518 --> 00:32:59,978
-See you.
-See you.

620
00:33:07,443 --> 00:33:10,113
-You're gonna carry all that?
-I've accumulated a lot.

621
00:33:10,196 --> 00:33:12,157
I remember that bag.

622
00:33:12,240 --> 00:33:14,701
Oh, this? The grass bag?

623
00:33:14,785 --> 00:33:16,452
It's literally a grass bag.

624
00:33:17,287 --> 00:33:20,373
-Hansan, here.
-What?

625
00:33:20,456 --> 00:33:22,375
We made it together.

626
00:33:22,458 --> 00:33:25,253
When did you do that?
Really?

627
00:33:26,004 --> 00:33:27,463
Thanks.

628
00:34:15,887 --> 00:34:17,263
Thank you.

629
00:34:18,264 --> 00:34:20,100
I'm going to treasure this.

630
00:34:22,603 --> 00:34:24,813
Don't make me cry, guys.

631
00:34:26,481 --> 00:34:28,108
I have to leave now!

632
00:34:28,692 --> 00:34:29,985
Sorry.

633
00:34:33,947 --> 00:34:36,950
I promise you that...

634
00:34:37,033 --> 00:34:42,706
one day you'll hear about me
as an architect somewhere.

635
00:34:45,626 --> 00:34:47,252
Watch me.

636
00:34:49,087 --> 00:34:52,090
-Watch me, okay?
-We will.

637
00:34:52,173 --> 00:34:53,508
Thank you.

638
00:34:54,509 --> 00:34:56,177
-Thank you.
-Thank you so much.

639
00:35:00,015 --> 00:35:01,516
I'm leaving now.

640
00:35:05,478 --> 00:35:08,189
-All right then!
-Thank you!

641
00:35:08,273 --> 00:35:09,775
See you around, Hansan.

642
00:35:11,526 --> 00:35:14,237
Okay, see you around!

643
00:35:14,320 --> 00:35:15,906
That was so anti-climactic.

644
00:35:32,088 --> 00:35:33,840
He's gone.

645
00:35:35,676 --> 00:35:37,260
He really is.

646
00:35:37,343 --> 00:35:40,055
-There's no one to lead us now.
-True.

647
00:35:40,138 --> 00:35:42,140
Are we gonna fall apart now?

648
00:35:42,891 --> 00:35:44,184
What?

649
00:35:46,019 --> 00:35:48,063
-Already? Isn't it too soon?
-Seriously?

650
00:35:48,146 --> 00:35:50,106
Wow, my heart stopped just now.

651
00:35:50,190 --> 00:35:51,650
What is it?

652
00:35:51,733 --> 00:35:55,779
Seriously, it's too soon!
What should I say?

653
00:35:55,862 --> 00:35:57,030
-Arman, Arman!
-Yes?

654
00:35:57,113 --> 00:36:00,283
<i>I'm moving in today.</i>

655
00:36:00,366 --> 00:36:01,702
Come in.

656
00:36:24,850 --> 00:36:27,477
-What's happening?
-Hey, there.

657
00:36:27,560 --> 00:36:30,772
You were bawling your eyes out
when Hansan was crying.

658
00:36:32,232 --> 00:36:35,443
I was like, "How much can she cry?"

659
00:36:41,366 --> 00:36:42,492
Yu, seriously?

660
00:36:42,575 --> 00:36:44,745
-She's bawling.
-Really?

661
00:36:44,828 --> 00:36:46,747
She's bawling.

662
00:36:46,830 --> 00:36:50,083
I never met the guy,
and I'm absolutely smitten by him.

663
00:36:51,084 --> 00:36:52,252
She said it.

664
00:36:52,335 --> 00:36:56,422
You know how alumni sometimes come back
in later episodes?

665
00:36:56,506 --> 00:36:58,842
Like, "Let's ask Hansan
if we need his help" type of thing.

666
00:36:58,925 --> 00:37:00,719
Like, "Ask Kojimasan."

667
00:37:00,802 --> 00:37:02,637
That's a good idea.

668
00:37:02,721 --> 00:37:05,265
Why do we have to console you?

